snippet.textDisplay: What's the point of VAR if it's not gonna make the right call on decisions like that? Without VAR I guarantee you Gomez falls over to buy the foul from the ref, but he thinks he doesn't need to because VAR will step in anyway. That's a disincentive for players to stay on their feet if VAR isn't going to back them up in situations like these, all because of this stupid "clear and obvious rule".
